summary:
My passion for geology comes from the strong interest in the history of the Earth and ‘deep time’. To be able to tell the story of the Earth based on the information rocks contain is a great inspiration for me. 
At the same time, I admire the challenge of applying scientific knowledge to large-scale problems the society presently is facing. In this respect, I am highly motivated to use my geological knowledge to contribute to exploitation of sustainable energy resources, such as geothermal energy.
